com.googlecode.cqengine.entity

Class MapEntity

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.entity.MapEntity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrimaryKeyedMapEntity

    public class MapEntity
extends Object
implements Map
    Wrapper for Map to allow efficient use in an IndexCollection. MapEntities can be created via QueryFactory.mapEntity(Map). Attributes can be created to read the entries in these maps, using QueryFactory.mapAttribute(Object, Class).

    This works by optimizing the performance of the hashCode() and equals(Object) methods - which may be called frequently during query processing. The hashCode of the wrapped Map will be cached to improve the performance of repeated invocations of hashCode(). The cached hashCode will be used in the implementation of the equals(Object) method too, to avoid computing equality entirely when the cached hashCodes are different.

    Note it is not safe to modify entries in maps which are indexed, although non-indexed entries may be modified safely. Alternatively, remove and re-add the Map to the collection.
